        "article": "Most Asian stock market indices ended on a negative note today. South Korea&#8217;s Kospi plunged 4.9 per cent, dragged by chip stocks. The index had fallen by more than 8 per cent earlier in the session, prompting the Korea Exchange to activate a circuit breaker and halt trading for 20 minutes. Taiwan&#8217;s Taiex shed 2.3 per cent, Japan&#8217;s Nikkei 225 fell over 2.1 per cent, China&#8217;s Shanghai Composite dropped more than 1.2 per cent, and Hong Kong’s Hang Seng dipped half a per cent. In contrast, Singapore’s Strait Times added nearly 1.6 per cent. Major European indices were trading on a mixed note today. London’s FTSE 100 rose 0.3 per cent, France’s CAC 40 gained nearly 0.3 per cent, while Germany’s DAX was trading more than half a per cent down, when reports last came in.",
